entries.s_14: I forgot who I was supposed to meet.
entries.s_15: What do you mean you forgot? It's the same guy who sent you to me; Hugo Eckener!
entries.s_25: Yes, you will. There is no point in delay, so you may as well proceed.
entries.s_34: What kind of name is Darkwalker for a criminal organization? I must speak with my superiors about this. A change is in order. Something more businesslike and less spooky.
entries.s_36: What are you waiting for? Go. The Skaak Tipper base awaits.
entries.s_37: Something is not right. Silence from my superiors is never a good sign.
entries.s_38: Finally, you're here. My superiors were very happy with your work against Borvo's gang and that lowlife thief, Kermollus. Now it is time to set your particular skills against the Skaak Tippers.
entries.s_39: What is it that you want me to do?
entries.s_40: You are going to kill as many Skaak Tippers as you can. Unless, of course, they kill you. If possible, you will also sabotage some of their database systems and steal some weapon research notes.
entries.s_73: You have done well enough, I suppose. That will be all.
